11-06T05:54:41.000-06:00","is_admin":false,"about":"F/OSS Developer and Arch Linux Developer doing packaging and security.\r\n\r\nInterested in Golang, development and supply chain security.","is_moderator":false,"karma":1494,"avatar_url":"/avatars/Foxboron-100.png","invited_by_user":"jelly","github_username":"Foxboron","twitter_username":"MortenLinderud"},"tags":["linux","nix"]},{"short_id":"yllllu","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yllllu","created_at":"2023-04-28T00:48:49.000-05:00","title":"We’re Afraid Language Models Aren’t Modeling Ambiguity","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2304.14399.pdf","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eAmbiguity is an intrinsic feature of natural language. Managing ambiguity is a key part of human language understanding, allowing us to anticipate misunderstanding as communicators and revise our interpretations as listeners. As language models (LMs) are increasingly employed as dialogue interfaces and writing aids, handling ambiguous language is critical to their success. We characterize ambiguity in a sentence by its effect on entailment relations with another sentence, and collect AmbiEnt, a linguist-annotated benchmark of 1,645 examples with diverse kinds of ambiguity. We design a suite of tests based on AmbiEnt, presenting the first evaluation of pretrained LMs to recognize ambiguity and disentangle possible meanings. We find that the task remains extremely challenging, including for the recent GPT-4, whose generated disambiguations are considered correct only 32% of the time in human evaluation, compared to 90% for disambiguations in our dataset. Finally, to illustrate the value of ambiguity-sensitive tools, we show that a multilabel NLI model can flag political claims in the wild that are misleading due to ambiguity. We encourage the field to rediscover the importance of ambiguity for NLP.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Ambiguity is an intrinsic feature of natural language. Managing ambiguity is a key part of human language understanding, allowing us to anticipate misunderstanding as communicators and revise our interpretations as listeners. As language models (LMs) are increasingly employed as dialogue interfaces and writing aids, handling ambiguous language is critical to their success. We characterize ambiguity in a sentence by its effect on entailment relations with another sentence, and collect AmbiEnt, a linguist-annotated benchmark of 1,645 examples with diverse kinds of ambiguity. We design a suite of tests based on AmbiEnt, presenting the first evaluation of pretrained LMs to recognize ambiguity and disentangle possible meanings. We find that the task remains extremely challenging, including for the recent GPT-4, whose generated disambiguations are considered correct only 32% of the time in human evaluation, compared to 90% for disambiguations in our dataset. Finally, to illustrate the value of ambiguity-sensitive tools, we show that a multilabel NLI model can flag political claims in the wild that are misleading due to ambiguity. We encourage the field to rediscover the importance of ambiguity for NLP.","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yllllu/we_re_afraid_language_models_aren_t","submitter_user":{"username":"jado","created_at":"2019-08-06T03:14:15.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Software Engineer, CompSci Grad Student (researching ML)\r\n\r\nloves plt, compilers, ml, rust\r\n\r\n[Website](https://jadon.io) | [GitHub](https://github.com/phase) | [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jado/)","is_moderator":false,"karma":1493,"avatar_url":"/avatars/jado-100.png","invited_by_user":"BruceM","github_username":"phase","twitter_username":"jadopoly"},"tags":["ai","pdf"]},{"short_id":"vvsfzy","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vvsfzy","created_at":"2023-04-27T12:27:05.000-05:00","title":"The future of programming: Research at CHI 2023","url":"https://austinhenley.com/blog/futureofprogramming2023.html","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"descrip